    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Draw random samples from a normal (Gaussian) distribution."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The probability density function of the normal distribution, first\nderived by De Moivre and 200 years later by both Gauss and Laplace\nindependently "
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "[2]_"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", is often called the bell curve because of\nits characteristic shape (see the example below)."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The normal distributions occurs often in nature.  For example, it\ndescribes the commonly occurring distribution of samples influenced\nby a large number of tiny, random disturbances, each with its own\nunique distribution "
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "[2]_"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Extended Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "Mean (\"centre\") of the distribution."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "float or array_like of floats",
              "inline": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "Mean (\"centre\") of the distribution."
                }
              ],
              "name": "loc",
              "type": "field_list"
            },
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "Standard deviation (spread or \"width\") of the distribution. Must be\nnon-negative."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "float or array_like of floats",
              "inline": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "Standard deviation (spread or \"width\") of the distribution. Must be\nnon-negative."
                }
              ],
              "name": "scale",
              "type": "field_list"
            },
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "(m, n, k)"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ", then\n"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "m * n * k"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " samples are drawn.  If size is "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "None"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " (default),\na single value is returned if "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "loc"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " and "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "scale"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " are both scalars.\nOtherwise, "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "flops.broadcast(loc, scale).size"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " samples are drawn."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "int or tuple of ints, optional",
